*WHAT?*

updated and extended version of browser dectection to be used in RAILS applications.
besides finding out the browser and OS version, it can also return if the "user agent" is
a bot, a mobile browser, an offline browser, etc. (still in TODO)

currently you can use it like this:

script/plugin install git://github.com/pboling/browser_detect.git

include BrowserDetectHelper
if (browser_is('mozilla') && browser_version>=2.0)
  puts "yay"
else
  puts "oh no!"
end

*INFORMATION*

see zytrax.com for a list of web browser names
http://www.zytrax.com/tech/web/browser_ids.htm

see also the user agent strings reference on developer.mozilla.org
https://developer.mozilla.org/en/User_Agent_Strings_Reference

